'''Shinmei Shrine''' (神明神社, Shinmei Jinja) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukui, Fukui|ja|福井市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|12=draft}}. The shrine’s former rank was that of a Prefectural Shrine, and it is currently a Beppyo Shrine under the jurisdiction of the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|12=draft}}. It is commonly referred to as "Oshinmesan" (おしんめさん) and enshrines {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|12=draft}}.
==History== According to the shrine's tradition, during the era of Emperor Daigo, a certain individual from Hokuno-no-shō of the Naikū Ashihara Mikuriya requested and received imperial permission to enshrine the deity of the Grand Shrine of Ise. In Enchō 2 (924), the divine spirit was enshrined at {{ill|Asuwa Shrine|ja|足羽神社|12=draft}}, and soon after, a shrine building was constructed at the current location for the deity.
The {{ill|Azuma Kagami|ja|吾妻鏡|12=draft}} records that in Kenkyū 3 (1192), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|12=draft}} granted the position of lord of the shrine to his sister's husband, {{ill|Ichijō Yoshiyasu|ja|一条能保|12=draft}}. The shrine enjoyed the patronage of successive lords, and the Edo Shogunate granted it a stipend of 100 koku. In Meiji 4, it was designated as a Prefectural Shrine.
==External Links== *[http://www.jinja-fukui.jp/detail/index.php?ID=20160119_155650 Shinmei Shrine] (Fukui Prefecture Shrine Office)
