{{Infobox religious building|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name=Shinmei Shrine | image=[[File:Shinmei Shrine (Fukui city).jpg|300px|Shinmei Shrine (Fukui city)]] | location=[[Fukui Prefecture|Fukui]] [[Fukui, Fukui|Fukui City]] {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 4-8-1 | coordinates={{Coord|36|04|07|N|136|13|10|E|scale:25000_region:JP-18|display=inline,title}} | deity={{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照皇大神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | shakaku=Former Prefectural Shrine・Beppyo Shrine | established=Enchō 2 (924) | honden={{ill|Shinmei-zukuri|ja|神明造|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[Steel plate roofing|鋼板葺]] | main_festival=May 5 (Shinmei festival) | map = {{location map|Japan Fukui Prefecture|label=Shinmei Shrine|float=center|relief=1|width=256}} }}
'''Shinmei Shrine''' (神明神社, Shinmei Jinja) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukui, Fukui|ja|福井市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The shrine’s former Rank was that of a Prefectural Shrine, and it is currently a Beppyo Shrine under the jurisdiction of the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is commonly referred to as "Oshinmesan" (おしんめさん) and enshrines {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
==History== According to the shrine's tradition, during the era of Emperor Daigo, a certain individual from Hokuno-no-shō of the Naikū Ashihara Mikuriya requested and received imperial permission to enshrine the deity of the Grand Shrine of Ise. In Enchō 2 (924), the divine spirit was enshrined at {{ill|Asuwa Shrine|ja|足羽神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and soon after, a shrine building was constructed at the current location for the deity.
The {{ill|Azuma Kagami|ja|吾妻鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} records that in Kenkyū 3 (1192), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} granted the position of lord of the shrine to his sister's husband, {{ill|Ichijō Yoshiyasu|ja|一条能保|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The shrine enjoyed the patronage of successive lords, and the Edo Shogunate granted it a stipend of 100 koku. In Meiji 4, it was designated as a Prefectural Shrine.
==External Links== *[http://www.jinja-fukui.jp/detail/index.php?ID=20160119_155650 Shinmei Shrine] (Fukui Prefecture Shrine Office)
