'''Shinmei Shrine''' (神明神社, Shinmei Jinja) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]], [[:en:Fukui (city)|Fukui, Fukui]], [[:en:Fukui Prefecture|Fukui Prefecture]]. The shrine’s former Rank was that of a Prefectural Shrine, and it is currently a Beppyo Shrine under the jurisdiction of the [[:en:Association of Shinto Shrines|Association of Shinto Shrines]]. It is commonly referred to as "Oshinmesan" (おしんめさん) and enshrines [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]].
==History== According to the shrine's tradition, during the era of Emperor Daigo, a certain individual from Hokuno-no-shō of the Naikū Ashihara Mikuriya requested and received imperial permission to enshrine the deity of the Grand Shrine of Ise. In Enchō 2 (924), the divine spirit was enshrined at {{ill|Asuwa Shrine|ja|足羽神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asuwa Shrine|qq=}}, and soon after, a shrine building was constructed at the current location for the deity.
The [[:en:Azuma Kagami|Azuma Kagami]] records that in Kenkyū 3 (1192), [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]] granted the position of lord of the shrine to his sister's husband, {{ill|Ichijō Yoshiyasu|ja|一条能保|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichijō Yoshiyasu|qq=}}. The shrine enjoyed the patronage of successive lords, and the Edo Shogunate granted it a stipend of 100 koku. In Meiji 4, it was designated as a Prefectural Shrine.
==External Links== *[http://www.jinja-fukui.jp/detail/index.php?ID=20160119_155650 Shinmei Shrine] (Fukui Prefecture Shrine Office)
